OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776885106
OL,3,CHalf of young Brits say they would
OL,4,Cnever fight for their country
OL,6,FHalf of young British people say they
OL,7,Fwould never fight for the country,
OL,8,Fwith only 38% saying they might do so
OL,9,F"under some circumstances," according
OL,10,Fto a new poll.
OL,12,FThe findings came from the second
OL,13,Fannual UK Youth Poll, released on
OL,14,FWednesday 22 April, which asked more
OL,15,Fthan 2,000 young people aged 16-29
OL,16,Fabout their opinions on a range of
OL,17,Fissues.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776885106
OL,3,CHalf of young Brits say they would
OL,4,Cnever fight for their country
OL,6,FResearchers from the University of
OL,7,FGlasgow's John Smith Centre, who
OL,8,Fproduced the poll, said the reluctance
OL,9,Fto go to war is a result of young
OL,10,Fpeople's growing pessimism.
OL,12,FWhile young people broadly reported
OL,13,Ffeeling positive about their personal
OL,14,Ffutures, the number who believed they
OL,15,Fwould be better off than their parents
OL,16,Fdropped from 63% in last year's poll
OL,17,Fto just 36% in 2026.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776885106
OL,3,CHalf of young Brits say they would
OL,4,Cnever fight for their country
OL,6,FThose who said they thought their
OL,7,Flives would be worse than their
OL,8,Fparents' more than doubled from 13% to
OL,9,F38% in the same period.
OL,11,F"The idea that the next generation
OL,12,Fwill have it better than previous ones
OL,13,Fhas been a founding belief for
OL,14,Fdecades," said Eddie Barnes, director
OL,15,Fof the John Smith Centre.
OL,17,F"Today's poll shows that the majority
OL,18,Fof this generation of young people no
OL,19,Flonger believe it to be true.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776885106
OL,3,CHalf of young Brits say they would
OL,4,Cnever fight for their country
OL,6,F"In those circumstances, it should be
OL,7,Flittle surprise that 50% say they
OL,8,Fwouldn't fight for the country under
OL,9,Fany circumstances.
OL,11,F"Or as many young people might put it:
OL,12,Fwhy fight for a country that isn't
OL,13,Ffighting for you?"
OL,15,FHe added that political leaders should
OL,16,Ftake note of the report's findings and
OL,17,Fproduce policies which "restore young
OL,18,Fpeople's faith in the future".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
